# Sepela Group Project Rules

## Tech Stack & Architecture
- Framework: Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI
- Animation: Framer Motion
- Form Handling: React Hook Form + Zod

## Critical Development Directives
- NEVER include or commit 'node_modules' under any circumstances. Respect .gitignore rigorously.
- Use the Next.js App Router convention: server components by default, add "use client" ONLY when interactivity (state, hooks, animations) is required.
- Always use the optimized Next.js Next/Image component (`<Image />`) for assets. Provide clear `alt` descriptions.
- All components must be fully responsive (mobile-first layout via Tailwind utilities).

## Code Style & Conventions
- Write clean, type-safe, self-documenting TypeScript code.
- Avoid using `any`. Define explicit interfaces or types for all component props and API responses.
- Implement functional components with explicit return types (`JSX.Element` or React nodes).
- Group Tailwind classes logically (Layout -> Sizing -> Typography -> Colors -> Interactive states).